---
title: Maple and Rosemary-Glazed Pork Cutlets with Apple Salad in a Creamy Dressing
description: Apple and maple syrup may sound like ingredients for a breakfast or a baking recipe, but we’ve managed to work those flavors into a quick and simple pork dish. The maple syrup gets stirred into the sauce for the meat, coating each cutlet in sticky deliciousness. The apple, on the other hand, is a highlight in the side salad, which also gets a boost from a creamy dressing. With couscous as a hearty base to back up all those flavors, you’ve got nothing less than sweet, sweet perfection.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/w10-r5-03f3f514.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/w10-r5-5a5ce4fbc28800337a57bcd2-851bd54a.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 700 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 55 g
  sugar: 23 g
  protein: 42 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 370 mg
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/w10-r5-5a5ce4fbc28800337a57bcd2
time required: 20 minutes
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), keeping greens and whites separate. Pick and finely chop enough @rosemary{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped) leaves from stems to give you 1 tsp. Halve, core, and dice @apple{1}(halved, cored, and diced).

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and @rosemary{1/2%tsp}(chopped). Cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Pour in @water{3/4%cup}. Bring to a boil, then immediately stir in @couscous{1/2%cup} and a large pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Remove from heat, cover, and let stand until tender, about ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @pork cutlets{12%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}. Season generously all over with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, about ~{2%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside on a #plate{}.

Reduce heat under pan to medium. Stir in remaining chopped rosemary, @white wine vinegar{1%tbsp} (we'll use more later), @maple syrup{1%ounce}, @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup}. Let simmer until thickened, about ~{1%minute}. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp}, then season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Return pork to pan, tossing to coat in sauce, then remove pan from heat.

Whisk together @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} and remaining @white wine vinegar{1%tbsp} in a #medium bowl{}. Add @mixed greens{2%ounce} and apple. Toss to combine. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}, then divide between plates. Arrange pork on top of couscous and drizzle with any sauce in pan. Garnish with scallion greens. Serve with salad on the side.